Fresh-eyes review complete on `src/blog/people/drafts/Madonna.md` — the notes are appended as a `FRESH EYES REVIEW (2026-07-18)` comment block at the bottom of the file. No body edits were made.

The two biggest issues I flagged:

1. **The draft skips 1999–2015 almost entirely.** It jumps from Ray of Light straight to the 2016 Billboard speech, so both marriages (Penn, Ritchie), the Kabbalah decade, the American Life video pullback, and the Rocco custody fight never appear. Relatedly, motherhood is used only as healing — the Malawi adoption controversies and her famously strict parenting (which mirrors her father's post-grief household) go unpressured, leaving the bell hooks critique stranded in 1992 when it has a natural extension into her family life.

2. **A promised payoff is missing.** The pre-write memo claims the Sex-book shame paradox (a Type 3 deliberately courting shame) is "Named in Rabbit Hole counterarguments," but the Rabbit Hole only covers the 8 and 4 cases — the sharpest self-objection in the file is invisible to readers.

Smaller notes: the 2016 Billboard speech and the 2015 Stern interview each get quoted five times (source fatigue), the "looked like X, was actually the operating system" reveal runs about four times, and the moral critics (hooks, Paglia) are faced while the more common "manufactured, can't sing" talent critique never is. On the plus side, the $35 timeline, the aging section's empathy turn, the ICU second-thought beat, and the Copacabana ending are all working and worth protecting in the next pass.
